This is a cursor rule to explicitly create compact layouts for a Salesforce object.
The correct file path for compact layouts is inside the folder of the custom object it belongs to.


Naming Convention: OBJECT_NAME_Compact_Layout

Take the same fields as specified in the Search Layout section of the object-meta.xml file of the custom object of which this compact layout is a part.

Example:
New custom object: 'Test Object'
Correct File Path: 'force-app/main/default/objects/Test_Object__c/compactLayouts/Test_Object_Compact_Layout.compactLayout-meta.xml'

Compact Layout xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<CompactLayout xmlns="http://soap.sforce.com/2006/04/metadata">
    <fullName>Test_Object_Compact_Layout</fullName>
    <fields>Name</fields>
    <label>Test Object Compact Layout</label>
</CompactLayout>

